<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36069c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36069c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36069c"> 69(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Croppies Acre</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;To avoid expensive interment, the authorities selected a piece of waste ground on the south side of Barrack Street, within about fifty paces of the Infantry Barracks, as a convenient repository for the corpses of the Irish rebels. This unhallowed spot was thenceforward known as &lsquo;<mark>Croppies&apos; Acre</mark>&rsquo; or &lsquo;Croppies&apos; Hole.&rsquo; &hellip;&rdquo; <small> James Collins, <a name="JCLO" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCLO"><cite title="source">Life in Old Dublin</cite></a> (l913) 58-59</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
